-- Indonesia May Allow Bulog to Import Rice to Build Up Reserves, Kontan Says
-- Yoga Rusmana
-- 2010-09-20T23:25:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-20/indonesia-may-allow-bulog-to-import-rice-to-build-up-reserves-kontan-says.html

          
          
             Indonesia may allow state food
company Bulog to import rice to build up stockpiles and to help
the government maintain domestic prices, Kontan reported, citing
Agriculture Minister Suswono.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
